description: From Middle English *foresenden (compare biforesenden), from Old English foresendan (“to send before”), equivalent to fore- +‎ send.

verbs.description: foresend (third-person singular simple present foresends, present participle foresending, simple past and past participle foresent)

examples: I presume to foresend my wife's maid with her linen, as the state of the city occasioneth me thereunto by increase of deaths, which many fear and flee.
